<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,188,213]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J." box="[341,651,188,213]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="319 - 350" refId="ref61842" refString="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J. (1986) The Polycirrinae (Polychaeta: Terebellidae) from Australia. Records of the Australian Museum, 38, 319 - 350. Available from: http: // www. australianmuseum. net. au / Uploads / Journals / 17666 / 185 _ complete. pdf (accessed 27 August 2014)" type="journal article" year="1986">Hutchings &amp; Glasby (1986)</bibRefCitation>
report the following variation in the 
<typeStatus box="[1061,1173,188,212]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">paratypes</typeStatus>
: 9–13 notochaetigerous segments, neurochaetae from segment 12–18, and dental formula of uncini MF:2–6:3–7 (
<tableCitation box="[1150,1233,223,248]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,239,296,319]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 1. Literature reports of intraspecific variation in the number of notochaetigerous segments and start of neuropodia in Polycirrus species. Mean of ranges indicated. Only reports indicating numbers of specimens examined are included." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF1B663CFF96FFDAFF66A275C6FEA290" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" tableUuid="DF1B663CFF96FFDAFF66A275C6FEA290">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
